        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-01-11 13:34:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nWe could introduce a group variable containing the subnet that can be used for infra to node/inter-node communication. and then filter ip addresses by this subnet each time, as opposed to setting ip of each node separately. then we could completely stop using ansible_default_ipv4. Do you consider this enough? And if so, how to name this variable?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
