        "timestamp": "2019-01-16 10:32:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> Ok, I ask differently: what issue this subnet solves where\n > designated ip  is insufficient? I just showed the reverse - when\n > subnet solution fails and designated ip is the solution.\n > \n > Where is the benefit from designated ip?\n\nWell, it is just a generic way of specifying where do nodes communicate. So, if at any point we would want something else than infra ip, we can use this subnet to find the correct one. And we do not need to specify multiple ips.\nWe could add overrides per host like kubernetes_ip or infrastructure_ip that would be optional. not sure.",
